quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  7,163,"Ask them, about the town which was situated on the sea shore, what happened when they transgressed in the matter of Sabbath. On the day of their Sabbath the fish appeared before them on the surface of the water but on the days other than their Sabbath they never came near them; thus did We tempt them because they transgressed"
  7,164,"Also remind them about the conversation among some of them, when some of them asked: \"Why do you admonish a people whom Allah will destroy or sternly punish?\" They replied: \"To be able to offer an excuse before our Lord that we did discharge our duty, and also in the hope that they may refrain from His disobedience"
  7,165,"However, when they disregarded the reminder, We delivered those who forbade evil and We overtook those who were wrongdoers with stern punishment because of their transgression"
  7,166,"But when after that they persisted in their forbidden ways, We said to them: \"Be detested apes"
  7,167,"Also remind them when your Lord declared that He would raise against them others who would afflict them with grievous torment till the Day of Resurrection. Swift is the retribution of your Lord, yet He is also the Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  7,168,We broke their unity as a nation and dispersed them into different communities all over the earth - some of them are righteous and others are the opposite - We tested them with both blessings and misfortunes so that they might turn to the Right Way
  7,169,"Then they were succeeded by an evil generation who inherited the Book; they indulged in the vanities of this nether life, saying: \"We expect to be forgiven\" assuming that they are favorites of Allah and somehow He will spare them. Yet if similar vanities come their way they would again seize them. Was not a covenant taken from them in the Book that they would not speak anything about Allah except the truth? And they have studied what is in the Book. Best for the righteous is the home of the hereafter, don’t you understand"
  7,170,"As for those who strictly observe the Book and establish Salah, surely We never let the reward of such righteous people go waste"
  7,171,"Remember when We suspended the mountain over them as though it was an umbrella and they feared it was going to fall on them and We said: \"Hold firmly to the Book that We have given you and be mindful of what is in it, so that you may guard yourselves against evil"